% Computer Science Department of Mississippi State University. This
% package assumes that the bibliography is generated by BibTeX using
% the Chicago style (chicago.bst). ** Other bib style may not
% work!**. However, you can hand code the bibliography with each
% bibitem looks like: 
%
%    \bibitem[\protect\citeauthoryear{Hoey, St-Aubin, Hu, and
%    Boutilier}{Hoey et~al.}{1999}]{hoey-et-al-1999}
%    Hoey, J., R.~St-Aubin, A.~Hu, and C.~Boutilier (1999).
%    \newblock Spudd: Stochastic planning using decision diagrams.
%    \newblock In {\em Proceedings of the Fifteenth Conference on
%    Uncertainty in Artificial Intelligence}.
%
% The first argument to \citeauthoryear is the complete list of
% last names of authors, the second argument is the ``short'' form of
% the list of authors, and third one is the year of publish.
% 
% In addition to the 4 citation commands provided by the original
% aaai.sty, I added another, \citeallauthors, that give the full list
% of authors in their last names. The original documentation (see
% below) seems to say that citations are enclosed in square brackets,
% but actually \begincite and \endcite is defined to be '(' and ')'.
%        

